ourneys. \n\t\t  New Ways of Working : Enable organisational changes and help clients transform into digital enterprises that scale effectively. \n\t\t  Technology Assessment &amp; Improvements : Assess client’s digital system, technology architecture, SDLC process and methodologies to discover area of improvements for better reliability, security, and scalability This role is ideal for you who possess:  \n\n \n\t At least 5 years of full-time experience in digital fields requiring strong problem-solving skills (e.g., product management, product research, business intelligence, data analyst, business analyst, management consulting, or corporate strategy) in leading digital companies or start-ups. \n\t A relevant tertiary degree in business, IT/computer science, psychology, engineering, or a related discipline. \n\t Ability to work with and lead multi-disciplinary teams, with a proven track record of coordinating projects across multiple work-streams. \n\t A mix of strategic and creative skills, with a highly structured approach in thinking and analysis. \n\t Expertise in quantitative analysis, with strong business acumen and a proven track record in data analysis and/or product research. Proven proficiency in data modeling and statistical analysis tools are highly regarded. \n\t Excellent communication skills in both written and verbal formats, capable of explaining complex concepts in simple terms clearly, concisely, and confidently. \n\t Experienced in presenting to key stakeholders, including senior management. \n\t History of building relationships and connecting with clients from various levels to align strategy and tactics, and share insights. \n\t Intellectual curiosity, resourcefulness, and exceptional attention to detail. \n\t A self-driven pursuit of excellence, consistently going the extra mile to elevate the quality of insights and deliverables. \n\t High adaptability and agility in tackling problems, with comfort in navigating uncertainty, complexity, a