{"job_title": "Network Expansion Specialist", "job_location": "South Jakarta, DKI Jakarta", "job_department": "General Services", "job_url": "https://www.kalibrr.com/c/gentem-learning-indonesia/jobs/264552", "first_seen": "2026-04-29 14:50:19", "base_salary": "0", "job_type": "Full time", "job_level": "Bachelor", "job_apply_end_date": "2026-05-02 17:00:00", "last_seen": "2026-03-04 08:26:17", "is_active": "True", "company": "Gentem Indonesia Lifelong Learning Group", "company_url": "https://www.kalibrr.com/id-ID/c/gentem-learning-indonesia/jobs", "job_board": "Kalibrr", "job_board_url": "https://www.kalibrr.com/id-ID/home", "job_age": "expired", "work_arrangement": "On-site", "desc": "Network Expansion Specialist General Services 🌟 We're Hiring: Network Expansion Specalist 🌟  \n\n At Gentem Lifelong Learning Group, we believe education opens doors to limitless opportunities. Through our brands Wall Street English, Genstarkids, and Indies we inspire lifelong learning for every generation. \n\n We’re looking for an experienced and driven  Network Expansion Specialist  to support our branch growth strategy across Indonesia. This role will be responsible for identifying, evaluating, and securing strategic locations for new centers/hubs, ensuring alignment with Gentem’s expansion roadmap and commercial objectives. \n\n  ✨ What You’ll Be Doing:  \n\n \n\t Acquire new centers/hubs by performing end-to-end site acquisition activities, including property lead sourcing, site survey, and landlord liaison. \n\t Build and maintain strong relationships with property agents, landlords, developers, and mall/building management. \n\t Conduct location feasibility analysis covering demographics, accessibility, visibility, competitor mapping, and commercial viability. \n\t Collect, verify, and ensure completeness of all legal and administrative documents required for the leasing process. \n\t Lead negotiations related to rental pricing, lease terms, fit-out periods, and commercial agreements. \n\t Prepare site evaluation reports and present recommendations to management. \n\t Collaborate with Legal, Finance, Operations, and Project teams to ensure agreements, payments, and implementation processes comply with company policies. \n\t Monitor the progress from site approval to handover for center development. \n \n\n ✨Key Responsibilities:  \n\n \n\t Site Survey &amp; Acquisition \n\t Property Sourcing &amp; Market Mapping \n\t Landlord &amp; Agent Network Management \n\t Lease Negotiation \n\t Contract &amp; Legal Documentation Support \n\t Cross-Functional Coordination for Branch Opening \n \n\n   \n\n  🎉 Why You’ll Love Working Here:  \n\n \n\t Be part of a high-performance culture that values growth, teamwork, and excellence. \n\t Competitive compensation, clear career pathways, and supportive leadership. \n\t Continuous career development through hands-on experience and learning opportunities. \n\t Career Growth: We love promoting from within! Your hard work will be recognized, and there’s always room to grow. \n \n\n  🌍 About Gentem  \n\n At Gentem Lifelong Learning, we empower people through education, opening doors to new opportunities. As the parent company of Wall Street English Indonesia, Genstarkids, and Indies, we uphold the values of Family, Integrity, and Excellence, fostering a culture of collaboration, trust, and outstanding results. Committed to lifelong learning, we create opportunities for growth at every stage of life. If you’re passionate about making an impact, you’ll fit right in. \n\n  💪 Ready to Make an Impact?  \nIf you’re an ambitious, results-driven partnership builder and event activation specialist, apply now and help us shape the future of education in Indonesia! 🛠️ What We’re Looking For:  \n\n \n\t Minimum 3–5 years of experience in site acquisition, expansion, business development, or commercial real estate. \n\t Strong network with property agents and landlords (experience in multi-branch retail, education, clinic, F&amp;B, or service industry preferred). \n\t Proven track record in securing strategic commercial locations. \n\t Strong negotiation and commercial analysis skills. \n\t Highly results-oriented with a track record of meeting expansion or acquisition targets. \n\t Willing to travel frequently and be highly mobile across assigned locations. \n\t Good understanding of lease structure, ROI calculation, and commercial feasibility analysis."}
