aborative approaches for learning, teaching and evaluation so as to improve the overall performance standards and competencies \n\t Implementation of specific center programs, initiatives and events \n\t Monitor and improve the quality of teaching and ensure high retention rate in each centers \n \n\n  🌟 Why This Role Will Define Your Career  \n\n \n\t National Impact: Join Indonesia's educational transformation as we expand our network of learning centers  \n\t Professional Growth: Lead in a high-autonomy environment with direct access to international best practices and continuous professional development \n\t Cultural Bridge: Play a crucial role in preparing Indonesian children for global opportunities while preserving local values \n\t Innovation Platform: Work with cutting-edge educational methodologies in an environment that encourages experimentation and creativity \n\t Community Legacy: Build lasting relationships with families and contribute to developing Indonesia's next generation of confident, adaptive learners \n \n\n  📔 About Genstarkids &amp; Gentem Indonesia  \n\n Genstarkids is a future-skills-based education brand focused on preparing children aged 4 to 12 for the world ahead. Our programs combine English, technology, entrepreneurship, and creative design to build the communication, confidence, and critical thinking skills that matter most in the 21st century. \n\n We are part of Gentem Indonesia, a lifelong learning group dedicated to empowering individuals at every stage of life to thrive in a fast-changing world. Gentem operates three leading education brands: \n\n Genstarkids Indonesia: Future-skills development for young learners \n\n Wall Street English Indonesia: English language training for adults and professionals \n\n Indies: Expert guidance for students pursuing overseas education \n\n At Gentem, we believe in building adaptable mindsets, lifelong learning habits, and real-world capabilities, starting from the earliest years. \n\n  💫 Ready to Make Educational History?  \n\n This isn't just a career move, it's your opportunity to pioneer educational innovation in one of Southeast Asia's most dynamic markets. If you're ready to lead with vision, build with purpose, and create lasting impact on Indonesia's educational landscape, we want to meet you. \n\n Join us in preparing today's children to become tomorrow's leaders, innovators, and change-makers. 🎓 What Makes You Our Ideal Leader  \n\n  Essential Qualifications:  \n\n \n\t Bachelor's or Master's Degree (preferred) in TESOL, Education, Psychology or related field \n\t Minimum 4 years in a leadership or coordinator role in education \n\t Excellent English communication skills (verbal &amp; written) \n\t Familiarity with international school systems or progressive education frameworks is a plus \n \n\n  Key Traits &amp; Skills:  \n\n \n\t Highly Proactive: Takes initiative and makes thoughtful decisions quickly without waiting to be asked, thriving in our fast-paced, purpose-driven environment \n\t Exceptional Communicator: High emotional intelligence with a bubbly, energetic personality that connects confidently with both children and parents \n\t Natural Problem Solver: Quick thinker and effective decision maker who can balance global educational trends with Indonesian cultural values and family expectations"}
